The paper proposes a learning-based algorithm for path planning for planetary exploration rovers, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) to plan paths directly from orbital images of planetary surfaces, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the algorithm is designed to improve the efficiency of executing exploration missions, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
